## What Your Employees Will Notice

- **Teams Phone intelligent call delegation (via Frontier program):** An AI assistant can now answer incoming Teams Phone calls and schedule follow-up appointments on behalf of users who are in meetings or unavailable. Users enrolled in the Frontier early access program will see this first. Communicate proactively so employees understand this is an opt-in, IT-governed feature, not an unsanctioned recording tool.
- **Copilot in SharePoint is on by default for licensed users:** As of mid-June, Copilot in SharePoint became enabled by default for all Microsoft 365 Copilot license holders. Employees may notice AI-assisted site creation, document generation, and natural-language search without having been explicitly told the feature was turned on. Proactive communication about what data Copilot can access will reduce confusion and support tickets.
- **Multi-line calling on Teams Mobile:** Employees with multiple assigned phone numbers can now manage all lines from their mobile Teams app, including unified call history. Useful for staff who manage personal and role-based lines.
- **OneNote multimodal capture coming to Android (Preview, September 2026):** Users on iPhone and iPad can already capture audio, images, and typed notes in a single Copilot-organized session. Android users will gain access in preview by August. Relevant to field teams, clinicians, or anyone capturing information away from a desk.
- **SSO prompts on managed Windows devices:** IT administrators can now suppress repetitive Microsoft sign-in prompts on managed Windows 11 devices using a policy setting. Employees on managed hardware should notice fewer interruptions when accessing Microsoft services.

*Sources: [Teams Blog — Intelligent Call Delegation](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-teams-blog/focus-on-the-teams-phone-calls-that-matter-most-with-intelligent/ba-p/4512533) · [SharePoint Blog — Copilot July 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-sharepoint-blog/what-s-new-in-copilot-in-sharepoint-july-2026/ba-p/4535420) · [Windows IT Pro Blog — SSO Admin Control](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/now-available-admin-control-for-sso-prompts-in-windows/ba-p/4534613)*

