## Cost & Licensing

- **Exchange migration budget decision is now urgent.** Organizations still on Exchange 2016 or 2019 must either migrate to Exchange Online (Microsoft 365 licensing cost) or deploy Exchange Server Subscription Edition before October. Both paths require budget, vendor coordination, and lead time. This is a board-level risk item if migration has not been funded.
- **Copilot Credits and consumption-based AI pricing.** Microsoft is hosting a live AMA on July 21 specifically to address Copilot Credits, the consumption model for AI experiences beyond standard seat licensing. Finance and IT leaders planning AI deployments should understand that some Copilot capabilities are priced per use, not per seat. Budget planning should account for this distinction.
- **Purview Data Lifecycle Management — archive OneDrive and SharePoint files.** A forthcoming feature (Preview August 2026, GA September 2026) will move inactive files to lower-cost storage automatically while keeping them discoverable and available to Copilot. Organizations paying for large SharePoint storage allocations should evaluate this as a cost optimization opportunity.
- **Copilot Studio autonomous agent sharing (Preview August 2026).** The ability to share autonomous agents with end users (run-only, no edit rights) will expand the reach of agents built by a small number of licensed makers. Organizations should evaluate whether this changes the licensing model for agent consumers before broad deployment.

*Sources: [Exchange Team Blog — ESU End Reminder](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033) · [Microsoft 365 Copilot Blog — Copilot Credits AMA](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-copilot-blog/join-us-live-understanding-copilot-cowork-and-managing-copilot/ba-p/4537935) · [M365 Roadmap — Purview Archive](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561208)*

